      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"3. OPAWA WEATHERLEY has some solid form under his belt and proved too classy last time to win by 8 lengths at this track in a handy 16.69 beating Gotcha Jasper. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings four times from six attempts. Steps back up to the top grade and looks the one to beat. 2. BROADWAY GEM will take beating coming off a scintillating 16.87 win at this track over 295m. Has really turned the corner of late and should be in this for a long way. 7. EVEREST SKY boasts a strong record this journey with 18 wins and 16 minors from 38 tries. Missed the frame latest (17.14) when fifth over 295m at this track in a Class 5. Much better than recent racing and can feature with the right run. 8. KEYARA picked up a cheque last time and is in the mix again. Usually has a strong finish over this distance.\",\"runners\":[3,2,7,8],\"exclusive\":false}",
